edu.memphis.ccrg.lida.framework.shared
Interface Node

All Superinterfaces:
Activatible, Condition, Initializable, Linkable
All Known Subinterfaces:
PamNode, RootableNode
All Known Implementing Classes:
NodeImpl, PamNodeImpl, RootableNodeImpl
public interface Node
extends Linkable, Condition

A Node represents a Concept in LIDA. It could be implemented in different ways for different parts of the system. For example could be pamNodes in the PAM and WorkspaceNodes in the workspace. Nodes with the same id represents the same concept so equals have to return true even if the objects are of different classes.

Author:
Javier Snaider, Ryan J. McCall
